cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DL, cs.CL, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - OCR (Optical Character Recognition) is a subfield of information retrieval, and this paper focuses on improving the accuracy of OCR text obtained from early printed books. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - OCR is also a subfield of computer vision, and the paper discusses using confidence-based voting to improve OCR accuracy. 
3. cs.DL (Deep Learning) - The paper mentions using OCRopus models, which are based on deep learning techniques. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with natural language text obtained from OCR, and discusses methods for improving the accuracy of this text. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses using cross fold training and voting to improve OCR accuracy, which are both machine learning techniques.
